knowledge_graph.title: Stamp duty
knowledge_graph.description: Stamp duty is a tax that is levied on single property purchases or documents. Historically, a physical revenue stamp had to be attached to or impressed upon the document to show that stamp duty had been paid before the document was legally effective. More modern versions of the tax no longer require an actual stamp.
